{"title":"2025 Sea Otter Classic: Ritchey Septimer Carbon Breakaway All-Road – John Watson","link":"https://theradavist.com/ritchey-septimer-carbon-breakaway/","date":1744480808000,"content":"<p><em>John caught up with Fergus from <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/ritchey/\" target=\"_blank\">Ritchey</a> at the <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/search/2025+Sea+Otter+Classic/\" target=\"_blank\">2025 Sea Otter Classic</a>. That morning, he showed up on a prototype Breakaway <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/all-road/\" target=\"_blank\">all-road</a> dubbed the Septimer…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><strong>The Radavist thanks <a href=\"https://1up-usa.com/\" target=\"_blank\">1-Up USA</a> for sponsoring our Sea Otter Classic coverage and our independent Reportage!</strong></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-17.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-17.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-18.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-18.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-18.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-18.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Fergus from Ritchey rolled into Sea Otter Classic to a bunch of my heckling. It was all from the heart. The guy really is a legend. Especially in the Bay Area with <a href=\"https://fyxo.co/en-us\" target=\"_blank\">fans</a> as far away as Melbourne, Australia. He’s a dedicated randonneur, completing Paris-Brest-Paris last year but his roots in the bike industry go back to his bike messenger days.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-13.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-13.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>As he arrived at the Laguna Seca Raceway on Thursday, I intercepted him on a new Ritchey prototype. It’s a total sleeper mule with nothing denoting its Ritchey DNA in terms of a logo mark, other than “Septimer” scrawled with a paint pen right next to the Breakaway system. I asked, “Mind if I snap a few photos?” and rolled it to my Sea Otter photo spot.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-8.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-8.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-20.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-20.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-20.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-20.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-19.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-19.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-19.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-19.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Septimer is a famous climb in the Alps of Switzerland. This all-road has clearance 700 x 48 mm tires, comes with a Ritchey carbon fork, and yes, a Breakaway system. For simplicity, the cable routing is external, making it easier to pack into a Ritchey Breakaway bag. As for the components, Fergus scoured Facebook Marketplace for the parts, landing the SRAM Red AXS and cable-actuated Growtac brakes, making it even easier to pack up and travel.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-22.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-22.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-22.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Ritchey-Septimer-Breakaway-22.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>From my rudimentary method, it looks like the seat angle comes in around 72.5º and the head angle around 72º, planting it firmly in the all-road category, balancing tire clearance with short chainstays and the ability to run a front derailleur, even with one of those AXS batteries. Neat.</p>\n<p>The Septimer will arrive later this summer from <a href=\"https://ritcheylogic.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Ritchey</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>The Radavist thanks <a href=\"https://1up-usa.com/\" target=\"_blank\">1-Up USA</a> for sponsoring our Sea Otter Classic coverage and our independent Reportage!</strong></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/ritchey-septimer-carbon-breakaway/\">2025 Sea Otter Classic: Ritchey Septimer Carbon Breakaway All-Road</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"3d51bf943f676e78dd519ebb2b30253a12bccf964520c84d8073b276c16c5eb4","category":"Cycling"}